name: Six Flags: Magic Mountain
description: Six Flags Magic Mountain is known as the “Thrill Capital of the World,” the 260-acre theme park features world-class roller coasters and over 100 rides, games and attractions for the entire family and was voted by USA TODAY readers as America's Best Theme Park.

name: Las Vegas Strip
description: The famous Strip, also known as the 'City Without Clocks,' is filled with light, glitz, and unlimited partying. The Las Vegas Strip is a stretch of South Las Vegas Boulevard in Clark County, popular amongst tourists and visitors for its concentration of resort hotels and casinos.

name: Freddy's Fazbear Dinner
address: Heriberto M. Aja 1028, 5 de Mayo, 44970 Guadalajara, Jal., Mexico
description: Freddy Fazbear's Pizza is a family pizza restaurant that features different animatronic mascots. The pizzeria is reminiscent of Chuck E. Cheese's and SnowBiz Pizza Place. The main mascots include Freddy Fazbear, Bonnie, Chica, and Foxy

name: O Block
description: It's a stretch of South King Drive where a young Michelle Obama once lived. They call it “O Block.”
